          <num>237-49</num>
          <heading>Unfair competition; penalty</heading>
          <content>
            <p>§237-49 Unfair competition; penalty.
No
taxpayer shall advertise or hold out to the public in any manner, directly or
indirectly, that the tax hereby imposed upon the taxpayer is not considered as
an element in the price to the purchaser.  Any person violating this section
shall be fined no more than $1,000 for each offense. [L 1935, c 141, §23; RL
1945, §5482; RL 1955, §117-47; HRS §237-49; gen ch 1985; am L 2024, c 76, §3]
